		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: is it possible to add a DS li-ion accumulator to DMG Gam</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Basically, you want to integrate a Li-on or Li-po cell battery and a charging circuit inside? <br /><br />A workaround solution is to use the DS as a charger, making an external link from inside the game boy to allow temporary connection to the DS's battery contacts. <br /><br />I did something like this a few years ago with a GB Pocket and a GBA SP...<br />That's what the RJ-11 jack is for. <br /><img src="http://bibin.gg8.se/image/xtr3.JPG" alt="Image" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


